- Personal Records now uses --pr-gold throughout (header, values, delta
  badges) instead of --primary (green) — the live session already uses
  pr-gold for every PR signal (HUD glow/pulse/badge, exercise-card ring),
  so this screen showing the same PRs in the generic 'good' green was a
  continuity break at the exact moment a user would want confirmation
  it's the same big deal that just flashed gold a minute ago.
- Personal Records' card gets a pr-gold tint + ring instead of plain
  bg-card, folded in from the plan's Phase 3 sketch since it's the same
  block of JSX already being touched here — splitting it across two
  commits would mean re-diffing these exact lines twice for no benefit.
- When the session includes PRs, the title and the stat-summary card get
  a static pr-gold accent (colored title, gold ring around the summary
  card) — a quiet, permanent callout rather than the live HUD's temporary
  glow/pulse, since this screen stays on screen instead of flashing once.
  No visual change on a no-PR session (confirmed via the uploaded
  screenshot, which is a no-PR run).

Scope note: WorkoutSummary.tsx itself (the stat/duration/muscle-map card)
is untouched — only wrapped from the outside in this route file — since
that component is also rendered by the History detail screen and wasn't
part of what changed here.

Verified via tsc/eslint against a clean main baseline — no new errors
introduced; confirmed no incidental reformatting of unrelated code in
this file leaked into the diff.
---
 src/routes/_app.workout.tsx | 29 +++++++++++++++++------------
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/routes/_app.workout.tsx b/src/routes/_app.workout.tsx
